To determine the change in water level, we calculate the volume of water displaced by the barge and ore when it sinks.

The total mass is \(15,000\,\text{kg} + 80,000\,\text{kg} = 95,000\,\text{kg}\), displacing \(95,000\,\text{kg}\) of water (since it sinks). The volume displaced is \(V = \frac{95,000\,\text{kg}}{1,000\,\text{kg/m}^3} = 95\,\text{m}^3\). The water level rises by \(\frac{95\,\text{m}^3}{6,633\,\text{m}^2} \approx 0.0143\,\text{m} = 1.43\,\text{cm}\), closest to **1.5 cm**.

